Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: The U.S. Department of Agriculture confirms to have suffered a cyber attack exploiting the MOVEit CVE-2023-34362 vulnerability.
Target Class: Public admin and defence, social security

Author: JokerSpy
Description: Researchers from BitDefender discover a set of malicious components, believed to be a part of an advanced toolkit designed to compromise macOS systems.
Researchers from Cyble discover numerous counterfeit LetsVPN websites, deliberately designed to distribute malware, masquerading as the genuine LetsVPN application.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: Honeywell International posts a notice on its website describing a data breach resulting from the CVE-2023-34362 vulnerability in MOVEit.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: East Western Bank joins the list of the victims of the data breach resulting from the CVE-2023-34362 vulnerability in MOVEit.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: Software firm Nuance joins the list of the victims of the data breach resulting from the CVE-2023-34362 vulnerability in MOVEit.
The Hatcher Agency files a notice of data breach after learning that a recent data security incident resulted in confidential consumer information being accessible to an unauthorized party.
Parker Wellbore files a notice of data breach after learning that hackers gained access to confidential information that had been entrusted to the company.
New Horizons Medical files a notice of data breach after learning that a recent data security incident compromised the personal information of 12,317 New Horizons patients.

Author: TimisoaraHackerTeam
Description: The Health Sector Cybersecurity Coordination Center issues an alert regarding a new relatively unknown ransomware group named TimisoaraHackerTeam that recently targeted an undisclosed U.S. cancer center.

Author: LockBit
Description: The Russia-linked ransomware group LockBit claims responsibility for a cyberattack on Indian pharmaceutical giant Granules India, and publishes portions of the data it allegedly stole.
Eftpos provider Smartpay reveals that criminals stole customer data in a ransomware attack.
MyShopCasa, an Italian e-commerce site has its database leaked.

Author: 8Base
Description: The Studio Legale Ranchino, an Italian law firm suffers a ransomware attack by the 8Base gang.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: The U.S. Office of Personnel Management confirms to have suffered a cyber attack exploiting the MOVEit CVE-2023-34362 vulnerability.
Target Class: Public admin and defence, social security

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: Australia's largest private health insurer Medibank Private discloses that a file containing names and contact details of staff members had been compromised after its property manager faced a cybersecurity breach due to the exploitation of the MOVEit CVE-2023-34362 vulnerability.

Author: Turk Hack Team
Description: The collective Turk Hack Team takes down the website of the Central Bank of Malta

Author: APT-C-35 AKA DoNot
Description: Researchers from Cyfirma discover three Android apps on Google Play (Device Basic Plus, nSure Chat, and iKHfaa VPN) used by the state-sponsored threat actors to collect intelligence from targeted devices, such as location data and contact lists.

Author: Killnet
Description: The pro-Russian Killnet hacktivist group claims to have taken down the network infrastructure of the European Investment Bank - EIB.
The reincarnated BreachForums site just has its user database stolen and published.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: Umpqua Bank confirms that it was impacted by the massive cyberattack targeting the MOVEit file transfer software.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: Approximately 16,000 members of Blue Cross Vermont health plans have their protected health information compromised in a January 2023 cyberattack carried out exploiting the CVE-2023-0669 zero-day vulnerability in Fortra’s GoAnywhere MFT file transfer solution and accessed and stole sensitive data such as names, birth dates, addresses, medical information, and insurance information. Around 5% of the affected individuals also had their financial information stolen.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: Software development firm Informatica reports that the Clop ransomware gang campaign obtained some files exploiting the MOVEit CVE-2023-34362 Vulnerability.

Author: APT28 (AKA BlueDelta, Fancy Bear, Sednit, Forest Blizzard and Sofacy)
Description: A joint investigation conducted by Ukraine's Computer Emergency Response Team (CERT-UA) and Recorded Future reveal that the APT28 group, linked to Russia's General Staff Main Intelligence Directorate (GRU), has breached Roundcube email servers belonging to multiple Ukrainian organizations, including government entities, exploiting the vulnerabilities CVE-2020-35730, CVE-2020-12641, and CVE-2021-44026.
Target Class: Public admin and defence, social security

Description: Researchers from Group-IB discover more than 101,000 ChatGPT user accounts stolen by information-stealing malware on various underground websites.

Author: State-sponsored APT aligned with China
Description: Researchers at Bitdefender reveal the details of Operation RedClouds, a campaign carried out by an advanced threat actor aligned with China, using a custom malware dubbed 'RDStealer' to automatically steal data from drives shared through Remote Desktop connections.

Researchers from AhnLab reveal that an unknown threat actor is brute-forcing Linux SSH servers to install a wide range of malware, including the Tsunami DDoS bot, ShellBot, log cleaners, privilege escalation tools, and an XMRig coin miner.

Author: Multiple threat actors
Description: VMware warns that the CVE-2023-20887 vulnerability, allowing remote code execution, is being actively exploited in attacks.

Author: Condi
Description: Researchers from Fortinet warn that a new DDoS-as-a-Service botnet called "Condi" is exploiting a vulnerability in TP-Link Archer AX21 (AX1800) Wi-Fi routers to build an army of bots to conduct attacks.
Car mount and mobile accessory maker iOttie warns that its site was compromised for almost two months to steal online shoppers' credit cards and personal information.
Hawaiʻi Community College discloses to be dealing with a ransomware attack.
Vincera Institute, a leading healthcare facility in Philadelphia, issues a notice regarding a recent ransomware attack
Community Research Foundation (CRF) files a notice of data breach, noting that a “Hacking/IT Incident” resulted in the confidential information of 30,057 individuals being leaked.
Kannact files a notice of data breach after determining that a recent data security incident resulted in unauthorized access to confidential consumer information that was in the company’s possession.
Stephen F. Austin State University is hit with a cyberattack.
A database with 25,000 records of the Italian jewelry firm Radà, is published on Breach Forums.
The City of San Luis discloses an unauthorized access to an employee’s email account that contained the protected health information of 6,848 individuals
Target Class: Public admin and defence, social security

Author: APT15 AKA Nickel, Flea, Ke3Chang, and Vixen Panda
Target: Foreign affairs ministries in Central and South American countries
Description: Researchers from Broadcom/Symantec unearth a new campaign by the Chinese state-sponsored group tracked as APT15, using a novel backdoor named 'Graphican'.
Target Class: Public admin and defence, social security

Description: Multinational shipping company UPS alerts Canadian customers that some of their personal information might have been exposed via its online package look-up tools and abused in phishing attacks.

Author: APT37 (AKA StarCruft, Reaper, or RedEyes)
Description: Researchers from AhnLab reveal the details of the latest campaign from the North Korean threat actor APT37 using two new custom malware strains dubbed 'AblyGo backdoor' and 'FadeStealer'.

Author: Russia
Description: Russian officials and diplomats have been coordinating an unusually organized and large-scale disinformation campaign to discredit reports that the nation is responsible for the June 6 collapse of the Nova Kakhovka Dam.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: Cybersecurity giant Gen, which owns well-known brands like Norton, Avast, LifeLock, Avira, AVG, ReputationDefender and CCleaner, confirms that its data was accessed through a cyber attack exploiting the MOVEit CVE-2023-34362 vulnerability.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: The Metro Vancouver Transit Police confirms to have suffered a cyber attack exploiting the MOVEit CVE-2023-34362 vulnerability.
Target Class: Public admin and defence, social security

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: The University of Missouri confirms to have suffered a cyber attack exploiting the MOVEit CVE-2023-34362 vulnerability.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: Telos, a US defense contractor specializing in cybersecurity, says that attackers downloaded its client data by exploiting the MOVEit transfer vulnerability.

Author: APT29 AKA Cozy Bear, Nobelium, Midnight Blizzard
Target: Governments, IT service providers, nongovernmental organizations (NGOs), and defense and critical manufacturing industries.
Description: Researchers from Microsoft detect increased credential attack activity by the threat actor APT29 (Midnight Blizzard) using residential proxy services to obfuscate the source of their attacks.

Author: ALPHV AKA BlackCat
Description: The ALPHV/BlackCat ransomware gang claims responsibility for the attack to Beverly Hills Plastic Surgery (BHPS).

Author: RedEnergy
Description: Researchers from Zscaler discover a new malware variant, RedEnergy stealer that fits into the hybrid Stealer-as-a-Ransomware threat category.

Author: Cyber Criminals in Ukraine
Description: Ukrainian cyber police disrupt a fake investment scam that involved stealing cryptocurrency from the online wallets of several Canadian citizens.

Author: REF9134
Target: Unknown cryptocurrency exchange located in Japan
Description: Researchers from Elastic reveal that an unknown cryptocurrency exchange located in Japan was the target of an attack to deploy the Apple macOS backdoor called JokerSpy.

Author: labs666
Description: A threat actor with the moniker labs666 active on a Russian-language hacker forum posts an advertisement offering access for sale to a military satellite operated by Maxar Technologies.

Author: labs666
Description: The same threat actor is also offering email account access to AT&T Corporation.

Author: MULTI#STORM
Target: Organizations in India and the U.S
Description: Researchers from Securonix discover a new phishing campaign codenamed MULTI#STORM targeting organizations in India and the U.S. by leveraging JavaScript files to deliver remote access trojans on compromised systems.

Author: Mudded Libra
Description: Researchers from Palo Alto Networks disclose the details of Muddled Libra, a threat group targeting large outsourcing firms with multi-layered, persistent attacks that start with smishing and end with data theft.
Forevermoto, an Italian e-commerce site dedicated to motorbikes has its database leaked online.

Target: Internet-exposed Linux and Internet of Things (IoT) devices
Description: Researchers from Microsoft discover a cryptojacking campaign brute-forcing Internet-exposed Linux and Internet of Things (IoT) devices, and using a trojanized OpenSSH version.

Researchers from Palo Alto Networks discover a variant of the Mirai botnet targeting almost two dozen vulnerabilities aiming to take control of D-Link, Arris, Zyxel, TP-Link, Tenda, Netgear, and MediaTek devices to use them for distributed denial-of-service (DDoS) attacks.

Author: PindOS
Description: Security researchers from Deep Instinct discover a new malicious Javascript dropper named PindOS that delivers the Bumblebee and IcedID malware typically associated with ransomware attacks.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: PricewaterhouseCoopers (PWC) discloses that a small number of clients had some files impacted in a cyber incident involving the MOVEit vulnerability

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: EY also confirms a MOVEit-related breach.

Author: Camaro Dragon (AKA Mustang Panda and LuminousMoth)
Description: Researchers from Check Point disclose the details of a cyber incident involving a hospital that was inadvertently affected by a self-propagating malware infection introduced to the healthcare institution’s network via a USB drive.

Target: U.S healthcare and public health sector
Description: The Health Sector Cybersecurity Coordination Center  warns that SEO poisoning attacks have been used "recently and frequently" against the U.S healthcare and public health sector.

Author: Volt Typhoon AKA Vanguard Panda
Description: Researchers from Crowdstrike detect a new campaign by the Chinese state-backed APT Volt Typhoon AKA Vanguard Panda exploiting CVE-2021-40539, a two-year old critical vulnerability in Zoho's ManageEngine ADSelfService Plus.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: Vitality Group International files a notice of data breach after discovering that a vulnerability in a file transfer software used by the company allowed attackers to access certain confidential consumer information. The breach is believed to be related to the MOVEit CVE-2023-34362 Vulnerability.
Desert Physicians Management (DPM) files a notice of data breach after determining that a recent cybersecurity incident compromised confidential patient information.
Atlanta Postal Credit Union (APCU) files a notice of data breach after learning that a recent ransomware attack compromised the confidential information of some bank customers.

Target: San Luis Obispo County Office of Education
Description: San Luis Obispo County Office of Education suffers a cyber attack.
Target Class: Public admin and defence, social security

Description: Limbach Facility Services confirms to have fallen victim to a cyberattack that affected the availability and functionality of its computer network.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: PBI Research Services (PBI) suffers a data breach with three clients (Genworth Financial, Wilton Reassurance, and CalPERS - California Public Employees' Retirement System) disclosing that the data for 4.75 million people was stolen in the recent MOVEit Transfer data-theft attacks.

American Airlines and Southwest Airlines, two of the largest airlines in the world, disclose data breaches caused by the hack of Pilot Credentials, a third-party vendor that manages multiple airlines' pilot applications and recruitment portals.

Target: Players of Super Mario 3: Mario Forever
Description: Researchers from Cyble discover that threat actors are distributing a trojanized sample of the Super Mario 3: Mario Forever installer, distributing the SupremeBot malware.
The Better Business Bureau (BBB) warns of scams involving fake Taylor Swift concert tickets.
Researchers from Phylum discover a new ongoing campaign aimed at the npm ecosystem that leverages a unique execution chain to deliver an unknown payload to targeted systems.
Senior Choice, doing business as The Atrium,  Beacon Ridge, and The Patriot reports a cyber incident.
Williamsport Home confirms that it experienced a data incident,

Author: Individuals in Ukraine
Description: The cyber police of Ukraine, in coordination with the national police, busts four call centers in the Kyiv and Lyiv regions that had been running investment scams targeting Azerbaijani citizens.
Activate Healthcare files a notice of data breach after learning that an unauthorized party was able to access confidential patient information following what appears to have been a cyberattack.

GeoSouthern Energy Corporation file a notice of data breach after learning that a recent cyberattack compromised confidential information belonging to current and former employees as well as their dependents.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: Harris Health System notifies patients and employees that some of their protected health information may have been compromised during a cyberattack exploiting the CVE-2023-34362 MOVEit vulnerability.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Target: Superannuation Arrangements of the University of London
Description: The Superannuation Arrangements of the University of London warns of a data breach occurred after the Cl0p ransomware gang exploited the CVE-2023-34362 Vulnerability.
The database of an undisclosed Italian airport with 7.8 million records is on sale in the dark web.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Target: New York City Department of Education (NYC DOE)
Description: The New York City Department of Education (NYC DOE) says hackers stole documents containing the sensitive personal information of up to 45,000 students from its MOVEit Transfer server.
Target Class: Public admin and defence, social security

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: The National Student Clearinghouse (NSC) is listed by the Cl0p gang among the victims of a data breach occurred exploiting the MOVEit vulnerability.
Target Class: Public admin and defence, social security

Author: SiegedSec
Description: Officials in Fort Worth, Texas, confirm that a website with government information was breached and accessed by a group of hackers but downplayed the severity of the incident.
Target Class: Public admin and defence, social security

Author: Individuals in Ukraine
Description: The Cyber Police of Ukraine raids nine fraudulent call centers that involved more than 200 operators working in the Kyiv and Dnipro regions, posing as bank and other financial institution employees to obtain credit and debit card data.

Petro-Canada gas stations across Canada are impacted by technical problems preventing customers from paying with credit card or rewards points as its parent company, Suncor Energy, discloses they suffered a cyberattack.
A distributed denial-of-service (DDoS) attack targets the servers of Diablo’s developer, Activision Blizzard.

Author: Anatsa
Target: Online banking customers in the U.S., the U.K., Germany, Austria, and Switzerland
Description: Researchers from ThreatFabric discover a new mobile malware campaign pushing the Android banking trojan 'Anatsa' to online banking customers in the U.S., the U.K., Germany, Austria, and Switzerland.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: Allegiant Air confirms that 1,405 people had information accessed through the exploitation of the MOVEit vulnerability.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: Jackson National Life Insurance discloses that 700K-800K of its customers were exposed in a  data breach stemming from the exploitation of the MOVEit vulnerability.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: Corebridge Financial files a notice regarding a data breach resulting from the CVE-2023-34362 vulnerability in MOVEit.

Gary Motykie, a plastic surgeon, notifies patients about a cyberattack and data theft incident, when the surgeon was contacted by a cyber threat actor who claimed to have accessed his IT systems and was in possession of sensitive patient information.
Barrow County in Georgia issued a breach notice about a breach of its email environment that occurred between March and August of 2022.
Target Class: Public admin and defence, social security

Author: Rhysida
Description: The Rhysida ransomware gang adds Fassi Gru to their leak site and claims to be in possession of 490 Gb of data.

Author: 8Base
Description: Legalilavoro, an Italian law firm, suffers a cyber attack from the 8Base ransomware gang.

Author: NoEscape
Description: The criminal gang NoEscape claims responsibility for an attack to the Italian financial provider CreditTeam, and leaks 12.1 Gb of data.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: Siemens Energy confirms that data was stolen during the recent Clop ransomware data-theft attacks using the zero-day vulnerability in the MOVEit Transfer platform.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: The Clop ransomware gang claims to have stolen data from MOVEit Transfer systems of another industry giant, Schneider Electric.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: The Clop ransomware gang claims to have stolen data from MOVEit Transfer systems of the University of California, Los Angeles (UCLA).

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: The Clop ransomware gang claims to have stolen data from MOVEit Transfer systems of the biopharmaceutical company AbbVie
Researchers from Bitdefender warn of tailor-made scams exploiting the OceanGate disaster.

Author: NoName057(16)
Target: Nearly a dozen major Ukrainian banks
Description: The pro-Russian hacktivists from the NoName057(16) collective take down several banks in Ukraine including four of the nation's largest commercial banks: First Ukrainian International Bank (PUMB), State Savings Bank of Ukraine (Oshchadbank), Credit Agricole Bank, and Universal Bank.

Author: Wagner
Description: Researchers from Cyble discover a new ransomware variant called Wagner, infecting user devices and inviting them to join the Wagner Group.

Author: ThirdEye
Description: Researchers from Fortinet discover a previously unseen infostealer named “ThirdEye”.
Precision Imaging Centers files a notice of data breach after the company discovered that it had been the recent victim of a cyberattack, giving hackers to confidential consumer data.
MAC Pizza Management files a notice of data breach after learning that confidential information belonging to thousands of people was compromised following a ransomware attack.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: U.S. government contractor Maximus is listed among the victims of the Clop ransomware gang campaign exploiting the MOVEit CVE-2023-34362 Vulnerability.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: AmeriSave Mortgage is listed among the victims of the Clop ransomware gang campaign exploiting the MOVEit CVE-2023-34362 Vulnerability.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: Agilysys is listed among the victims of the Clop ransomware gang campaign exploiting the MOVEit CVE-2023-34362 Vulnerability.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: The College of American Pathologists is listed among the victims of the Clop ransomware gang campaign exploiting the MOVEit CVE-2023-34362 Vulnerability.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: Chuck E. Cheese is listed among the victims of the Clop ransomware gang campaign exploiting the MOVEit CVE-2023-34362 Vulnerability.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: The Boston Globe joins the list of the victims of the Clop ransomware gang campaign exploiting the MOVEit CVE-2023-34362 Vulnerability.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: Datasite files a notice of data breach following a third-party data breach occurred exploiting the MOVEit CVE-2023-34362 Vulnerability.

Target: Italian Ministry of Economy and Finance
Description: A subpage of the website of the Italian Ministry of Economy and Finance (the welfare fund), is defaced to advertise a gambling site.
Target Class: Public admin and defence, social security

Author: BlackBasta
Description: The BlackBasta ransomware gang claims responsibility for a cyber attack to Giambelli, an Italian Real Estate firm.

Author: 8Base
Description: Researchers from VMware/Carbon Black discover a spike of activities by the 8Base ransomware gang.

Author: Akira
Description: The Akira ransomware operation releases a Linux encryptor to encrypt VMware ESXi virtual machines in double-extortion attacks against companies worldwide.

Author: Andariel (AKA Stonefly)
Description: Researchers from Kaspersky discover a previously undocumented remote access trojan (RAT) named 'EarlyRAT,' used by Andariel, a sub-group of the Lazarus North Korean state-sponsored hacking group.

Author: Attackers allegedly affiliated with the Wagner Group
Description: A group of previously unknown attackers allegedly affiliated with the Wagner Group claims responsibility for a cyberattack on the Russian satellite communications provider Dozor-Teleport and its parent company Amtel Svyaz.

Author: SiegedSec
Description: Hacktivists from the SiegedSec collective dump some data from the Nebraska Supreme Court.
Target Class: Public admin and defence, social security

Author: SiegedSec
Description: Hacktivists from the SiegedSec collective dump some data from the South Dakota Boards and Commissions
Target Class: Public admin and defence, social security

Author: SiegedSec
Description: Hacktivists from the SiegedSec collective dump some data from the South Dakota Boards and Commissions
Target Class: Public admin and defence, social security

Author: SiegedSec
Description: Hacktivists from the SiegedSec collective dump some data from the Pennsylvania Provider Self-Service
Target Class: Public admin and defence, social security

Author: SiegedSec
Target: South Carolina Criminal Justice Information Services (CJIS)
Description: Hacktivists from the SiegedSec collective dump some data from the South Carolina Criminal Justice Information Services (CJIS)
Target Class: Public admin and defence, social security

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: Sony is listed by the Cl0p gang among the victims of a data breach occurred exploiting the MOVEit vulnerability.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: Cognizant is listed by the Cl0p gang among the victims of a data breach occurred exploiting the MOVEit vulnerability.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Target: U.S. Department of Health and Human Services (HHS)
Description: The U.S. Department of Health and Human Services (HHS) is listed by the Cl0p gang among the victims of a data breach occurred exploiting the MOVEit vulnerability.
Radeal, the Polish developer of the Android stalkerware ‘LetMeSpy’, informs users that their personal information and collected data was stolen as a result of a cyberattack.

Author: NoName057(16)
Description: The pro-Russian hacktivists from the NoName057(16) collective take down the website of the Swedish railway carrier SJ AB

Author: NoName057(16)
Description: The pro-Russian hacktivists from the NoName057(16) collective take down the website of the Swedish Financial Supervisory Authority, Finansinspektionen (FI).
Target Class: Public admin and defence, social security

Author: APT35 (aka Charming Kitten, Imperial Kitten, or Tortoiseshell)
Description: Researchers from Volexity discover a campaign by the Iranian threat actor Charming Kitten attempting to distribute the POWERSTAR backdoor via a spear-phishing campaign involving an LNK file inside a password-protected RAR file.

Author: Triada
Description: Researchers at Check Point uncover a trojanized version of the widely-used Telegram messenger, containing embedded malicious code associated with the Triada trojan.
Wealth Enhancement Group (WEG) files a notice of data breach after discovering that an unauthorized party was able to access a standalone server in one of the company’s advisor team offices.
Citi Trends files a notice of data breach after discovering that an unauthorized party was able to access confidential employee information stored on the company’s IT network.

Roosevelt University (RU) files a notice of data breach after discovering that an unauthorized actor was able to access confidential student and prospective student information in the school’s possession.
Researchers from Akamai discover a proxyjacking campaign targeting vulnerable SSH servers, then launching Docker services that share the victim's bandwidth for money.

Researchers from Wordfence disclose that attackers are exploiting CVE-2023-3460, a zero-day privilege escalation vulnerability in the 'Ultimate Member' WordPress plugin to compromise websites by bypassing security measures and registering rogue administrator accounts.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: The law firms Kirkland & Ellis is listed by the Cl0p gang among the victims of a data breach occurred exploiting the MOVEit vulnerability.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: The law firms K&L Gates is listed by the Cl0p gang among the victims of a data breach occurred exploiting the MOVEit vulnerability.

Author: Turkey
Description: Researchers from Google terminate 14 YouTube channels part of a coordinated influence operations linked to Turkey and sharing content in Turkish supportive of the AK Party.

Author: Turkey
Description: Researchers from Google terminate 68 YouTube channels part of a coordinated influence operations linked to Turkey and sharing content in Turkish supportive of the Nationalist Movement Party (MHP) and Victory Party.

Author: Iran
Description: Researchers from Google terminate 14 YouTube channels part of a coordinated influence operations linked to Iran and sharing content about a variety of topics including content supportive of Palestine and critical of Israel.

Author: Iran
Description: Researchers from Google terminate 3 YouTube channels part of a coordinated influence operations linked to Iran and sharing content in French and English related to Iranian hack-and-leak operations.

Author: Russian consulting firm
Description: Researchers from Google terminate 337 YouTube channels part of a coordinated influence operations linked to a Russian consulting firm and sharing content in Russian supportive of Russia and Russian President Vladimir Putin and critical of Ukraine, NATO and the West.

Author: Russia
Description: Researchers from Google terminate 7 YouTube channels part of a coordinated influence operations linked to Russia, and sharing content in Russian that promoted the Wagner Group and Yevgeny Prigozhin.

Author: Spain
Description: Researchers from Google terminate 35 Youtube channels part of a coordinated influence operations linked to Spain, and sharing content in Spanish that was critical of the Spanish government.

Author: Mexico
Description: Researchers from Google terminate 188 YouTube channels part of a coordinated influence operations linked to Mexico, sharing content in Spanish supportive of the Morena party and Senator Ricardo Monreal.

Author: China
Description: Researchers from Google terminate 9,599 YouTube channels and 3 Blogger blogs part of a coordinated influence operations linked to China, uploading spammy content in Chinese about music, entertainment and lifestyle. A very small subset uploaded content in Chinese and English about China and U.S. foreign affairs.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: The Minnesota business firm The Harrington Company is added to the Clop ransomware leak site of the victims of the MOVEit breach.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: City National Bank in Miami, Florida is added to the Clop ransomware leak site of the victims of the MOVEit breach.

Author: BlueNoroff (part of the Lazarus Group)
Description: Researchers from Elastic detect a new variant of the RUSTBUCKET malware with improved capabilities to establish persistence and avoid detection by security software.

Target: Law firms, Healthcare and Investment Firms
Description: Researchers from Morphisec Labs discover an active GuLoader campaign that primarily focuses on law firms, along with healthcare and investment firms, specifically within the United States
The head of UAE Cyber Security reveals that, earlier in 2023, Israel aided the United Arab Emirates (UAE) in helping repel a major distributed denial-of-service (DDoS) attack.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: Bristol Myers Squibb files a notice regarding a data breach resulting from the CVE-2023-34362 vulnerability in MOVEit.

Advanced Medical Management files a notice of data breach after discovering that portions of the company’s IT network that were designed and maintained by third-party vendors were accessible to an unauthorized party.
John & Kira’s and Smithfield Specialty Foods each file a notice of data breach after learning about an incident that occurred at CommerceV3, a company that provides various web-hosting services.

The Henrietta Johnson Medical Center postes notice that some patient data was involved in a breach at Delaware Health Network (DHN), a healthcare-controlled network provider and electronic health records management provider that provides services to Henrietta Johnson Medical Center (HJMC) and other entities.

Author: Rhysida
Description: The Lumberton Independent School District is hit with a Rhysida ransomware attack.

Author: Cyclops
Description: A relatively new ransomware group, Cyclops, claims to have attacked Atherfield Medical & Skin Cancer Clinic in Australia:

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: Talcott Resolution Life Insurance Company is listed among the victims of the Cl0p ransomware gang exploiting the CVE-2023-34362 Vulnerability.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: The University of Southern Illinois is listed among the victims of the Cl0p ransomware gang exploiting the CVE-2023-34362 Vulnerability.
The Lebanon School District is hit by a ransomware attack.

Author: LockBit 3.0
Description: Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company (TSMC), the world’s largest contract chipmaker, confirms it’s experienced a data breach after being listed as a victim by the LockBit ransomware gang. However the Ransomware gang hit one of the company’s IT hardware suppliers, named as Kinmax Technology.

Author: Anonymous Sudan
Target: EFTPS.gov (U.S. Treasury Department's Electronic Federal Tax Payment System)
Description: The U.S. Cybersecurity and Infrastructure Security Agency (CISA) warns of ongoing distributed denial-of-service (DDoS) attacks after U.S. organizations across multiple industry sectors are hit.
Target Class: Public admin and defence, social security

Author: Anonymous Sudan
Description: Anonymous Sudan claims to have taken down the website of the U.S. Commerce Department.
Target Class: Public admin and defence, social security

Author: Anonymous Sudan
Description: Anonymous Sudan also claims responsibility for another DDoS attack that targeted Stripe's dashboard for managing business payments, refunds, and operations.

Author: ALPHV AKA BlackCat
Description: Researchers from Trend Micro discover a malvertising campaign from the BlackCat ransomware gang to lure people into fake pages that mimic the official website of the WinSCP file-transfer application for Windows but instead push malware-ridden installers.
Cambridgeshire Police says they are in the “early stages” of investigating a “data breach” involving exam boards Pearson Edexcel.
Cambridgeshire Police says they are also investigating a “data breach” involving exam boards OCR
Police are also investigating a cyber-attack at England’s largest exam board AQA, the third board to be targeted.

Author: Meduza Stealer
Description: Researchers from Uptycs discover Meduza Stealer, a new Windows-based information stealer actively being developed by its author to evade detection by software solutions and targeting 19 password manager apps, 76 crypto wallets, 95 web browsers, Discord, Steam.
Researchers from Inky discover a phishing campaign embedding QR codes into their bodies to avoid detection.

Author: ALPHV AKA BlackCat
Description: Researchers from Trend Micro discover a new campaign by the ALPHV/BlackCat ransomware gang, mimicking the website of a well-known Windows application WinSCP, distributed via malvertising, to infect victims.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Target: Maryland's Department of Health and Human Services
Description: The Maryland's Department of Health and Human Services is listed among the victims of the Cl0p ransomware gang exploiting the CVE-2023-34362 Vulnerability.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: United Bank files a notice regarding a data breach within a third-party software tool. It is suspected that the breach involves the CVE-2023-34362 vulnerability in MOVEit.
Gates Corporation files a notice of data breach after confirming that the company was the victim of a ransomware attack.
Imagine360 files a notice of data breach after discovering two data breaches at third-party vendors, both involving two different file transfer software programs (Citrix and Fortra).

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: Clearwater Credit Union files a notice of data breach after discovering the personal information of 25,660 individuals was leaked as a result of the massive MOVEit vulnerability.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: Union Bank and Trust Company (UBT) files a notice of data breach after discovering the personal information of 25,660 individuals was leaked as a result of the massive MOVEit vulnerability.

Mount Desert Island Hospital (MDIH) files a notice of data breach after discovering that an unauthorized party had gained access to confidential patient information stored on the company’s computer network.
ARx Patient Solutions files a notice of data breach after discovering that an employee’s M365 email account was accessed by an unauthorized party.

Author: Rhysida
Description: The University of Salerno is hit with a Rhysida ransomware attack.

Author: Clop AKA Lace Tempest, TA505 and, FIN11
Description: Realm IDX, a diagnostics company, confirms to have suffered a data breach occurred exploiting the MOVEit CVE-2023-34362 vulnerability.

Target: Arizona Health Care Cost Containment System (AHCCCS)
Description: The Arizona Health Care Cost Containment System (AHCCCS) discloses a data breach compromising over 2,000 Medicaid members.
Target Class: Public admin and defence, social security

Description: South Suburban Surgical Suites reports a breach of a legacy Microsoft Office 365-hosted business email account.

Author: BianLian
Description: The BianLian Ransomware gang claims responsibility for the alleged Piramal Group cyber attack, listing the Indian business conglomerate as a victim on the ransomware gang’s leak site.
